For tumor implantation, C57BL/6 male mice were injected subcutaneously with 1 × 106 TRAMP-C2 cells in the right hind flank. The experimental mice were divided into treatment groups (n=10). Animals were monitored for tumor growth. As tumors became detectable, electronic calipers were used to measure the length and width of the tumor and the tumor volumes were calculated by applying the following equation: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
