				\begin{document}$${\text {volume\;{(V)}}} \; = {\frac{4}{3}\times{3.14159}\times\left(\frac {{\text{length}}}{2}\times\frac {{\text{width}}}{2}\times\frac {{\text{width}}}{2}\right)}$$\end{document}volume\;(V)=43×3.14159×length2×width2×width2. Under the University of Pennsylvania Animal Care and Use Committee guidelines mice are sacrificed when tumor diameter reaches 2 cm, or when tumors became ulcerated. Survival differences between groups were analyzed by Students t test, p > 0.05 is considered significant.
